# Regex patterns matched against the full URL; one per line.
# Each entry MUST have a comment explaining why.

# opentelemetry.io hosts the authoritative OTel semantic-conventions spec.
# The site's CDN intermittently rate-limits or TLS-rejects requests from
# GitHub Actions runners, producing transient "Connection failed" /
# "TLS handshake failed" errors on PR CI runs while returning 200/301 for
# everyone else (verified via curl outside CI). The URLs are referenced
# in CHANGELOG.md as historical references; removing them would lose
# auditability, and the stable docs path is a strong guarantee they'll
# keep resolving. Ignoring them in lychee while keeping the reference
# is the pragmatic trade-off.
# Revisit: if OTel moves their specs site, drop this and re-verify.
^https://opentelemetry\.io/docs/specs/semconv/.*$
